Verify that a model with invalid attributes can be determined; e.g.

  bookmark = Bookmark.new(invalid_attributes)
  expect(bookmark.valid?).to be_false

and:

  bookmark = Bookmark.new(valid_attributes)
  expect(bookmark.valid?).to be_true
  
  
rake db:drop:all db:create:all db:migrate db:test:prepare

In Rails, the typical place for adding methods to existing classes is to use the config/initializers/ folder.  So, for adding a shuffle method to String, you'd have:

config/initializers/string.rb

with:

class String
  def shuffle
    # TODO: Your implementation here
  end
end

